### Steps to reproduce

Set ExpansionPanel.canTapOnHeader = true, ExpansionPanelList.expandIconColor will be ignored, and the IconButtonTheme.foregroundColor disabled state will instead be used.

[This issue](https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/138904) says it is working as intended because it "is grey because it is disabled when canTapOnHeader is true", however, it shouldn't appear disabled as it is an indication to the user that it is expandable, and even if that particular button is disabled, it should appear enabled since tapping there will perform the expand/collapse action. It is a visual-only bug.

