### Steps to reproduce

1. Create a TextField
2. Create a class inherited from TextEditingController
3. Set it as the controller for the TextField
4. Implement buildTextSpan where a set of words are displayed as WidgetSpan
5. Write in the TextField the words that will be displayed as WidgetSpan
6. Play a bit with the selection position moving forward and backwards
7. Delete or enter some characters a few positions after ending the WidgetSpan

### Expected results

The characters deleted should be the ones you are selection or are inmediately aside the cursor.

### Actual results

The cursor position is calculated as if widgets were a single character, while it is displayed as if their length were their string's size.
For example, if I have this tring "AABBCCDD" where "BBCC" is displayed with a WidgetSpan and the cursos is positioned between the two "D", when I press return it will delete the second "B" instead of the first "D".

