### Steps to reproduce

When addressing https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/150769, @delfme raised this as a second issue. I create this as a separate issue for better tracking.

1. Create a sheet action named `CustomBottomSheetAction` which implements CupertinoActionSheetAction. Inside this build body, wrap child with a `GestureDetector`.
2. Use it inside CupertinoActionSheet and see that action can't be clicked

I think this is related to https://github.com/flutter/flutter/pull/149471.

### Expected results

The custom action can be clicked as before (it is working on stable channel). Only experience this on Flutter master channel.

### Actual results

The custom action can't be clicked

